Welcome to Online Searches for Gravitational Waves in coincidence with
Gamma-ray Bursts.

gwgrbprocessor fully automates the processes of Online Searches for
Gravitational Waves in coincidence with Gamma-ray Bursts. It makes query to
GraceDB External events, annotates it, checks for required gravitational-wave
data, launches LIGO/Virgo data analysis, diagnoses failures, aids in loudest
trigger data-quality follow-ups, generates detector-status and result Circulars,
initiates follow-up advocacy and many more.

More information can be found at the website:
   <https://wiki.ligo.org/viewauth/Bursts/GRBGroup>

To install gwgrbprocessor locally:
   python setup.py install --prefix=/path-to-install-directorys

The most current gwgrbprocessor development version is available from
the git repository:

   git clone https://github.com/dipongkar/gwgrbprocessor
